storyInfo: The Trilby Asher tries to cut Enciodes off from his defensive ploy, but doesn't foresee that Sciurus has made her own arrangements. Degenbrecher fends off an entire army while not allowing them an inch, and as he watches the odds stack against her, Enciodes's ace in the hole finally arrives, averting the crisis.

attributes.content: Erk...
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier A

attributes.content: Ghakh!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier B

attributes.content: Watch out—!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier C

attributes.content: Next.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Heyaaaargh!!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier D

attributes.content: Reporting in, sir!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: With Colonel Harold's support, we've brought all our current casualties back to safety!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: However, as things stand for us, we still don't have a way to strike the enemy where it hurts!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Charge!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Make use of your arms! The enemy is one soldier! Surround her!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Sir, wouldn't it be better for us to divert around her?
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: She's an army of one! She's got not hope of holding us if we just widen the front!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: You... gormless idiot!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Was that meant to be a revelation to me?
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Then why...
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: They didn't give you eyes in your head for nothing!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: You saw what our men on Kjeragandr's doorstep were attempting, didn't you? All of them as smart as you, off to break the perimeter from somewhere else!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Compare that to the rest! Are they in as near as bad a state?
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Sir, you're not telling me...
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Private, I don't know what the hell I could be telling you—DUCK!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Guh...!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: My hand slipped.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Done gossiping?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: When in the hell did you get here...?!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Just now.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: If you were counting on a few dozen men there to stop me, then you really weren't ready for me.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Tsk! Monster incarnate...
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: A few dozen won't do the trick? Then surely a few hundred will. How about over a thousand?
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: You'll learn. In the face of a real army, there is no army of one—
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Clench your teeth.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Keep your mouth shut when I hit you.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You don't want to bite your tongue.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: A bitter slice of wind whistles through.
One against two thousand should be the pinnacle of despair. Her golden eyes tell of no such qualms—stern and still and steady.
She is the predator without dispute. She is the ruler over this battlefield.
Slight the affairs of one Ms. Degenbrecher, dare to even begin to scorn her, and you too are an affront to her.
—You'd best hope your own life meant as little to you.
Steady now, Madam Degenbrecher!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: If my subordinates have cocked up talks with you, then it falls to me to apologize in their stead.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: And how long can you shield them for?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Well! Ha-hah. Might I suggest... until I die a soldier's death?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: *hiss*...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I'm no match for your namesakes! Clearly I've not the horns to lock with you in a fight.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Do you recall, Madam Degenbrecher, when I asked after your name?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I no longer see any time like the present. Might I be elucidated?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: You have the guts to stall with me?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: *wheeze*, *wheeze*!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Two of a mind can spare a word in no-man's land! It is done, you know... it's the done thing!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I barely even remember my real name. You can pretend I never had one.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Plenty of people in Leithanien's ruined streets without a name or a home.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: —I'd heard tell of your Leithanian birth, but never had I known that to be your life's story...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I once read in the dailies how you pilgrimed home there. Adulation of the masses. Dinners with the upper crust.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Throw a trophy at a burdenbeast and watch them love it too. They don't tell the difference.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Don't let it fool you.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: It's not a place where names change anything. No one's going to ask you when you're down in the gutter with the wastewater.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Yet now you've a name with... such power.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Power?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Not exactly.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: It was a sunny day.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: A Gendarmerie patrol rounded up anyone with no place to go on the corner. One of them was carrying a strange weapon I'd never seen before. No point. No edge.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: No fine combat technique. No deep method to it.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: No simpler way to bludgeon. No part was anything of mention. I watched as he took that thing to anybody who tried to resist, and caved in their skulls.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: From that moment on, it's been clear to me what I have.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Not a code, or a creed, or a technique. Nothing that sounds nice out loud.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: It's violence.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: So that day, I named myself.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: I am what I wield.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: There's a Minoan school of thought, where they hold violence and victory as sisters. The two are inseparably close—they make one another.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: A look at you, and I could be convinced.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Madam Degenbrecher, if you're violence in the flesh like you say... then who, exactly, is your victory dedicated to?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: And finally, one last little quibble from me—though I do think—it may not be worth much in the asking.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: That Gendarmerie who first enlightened you—was victory a sister to him too?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I did like his degenbrechers.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Good to use, but broke too fast.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Just like you, Craigavon.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Your arm's almost gone.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Hush-hush, Madam Degenbrecher! Spare me the truth.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I do happen to be command of my own regiment. A little dignity, if you please...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Were the clock turned back thirty... no, just twenty years, I'd only be too glad your opponent.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: But as it stands, and though I hate to admit it, the reality's all too obvious—I'm one of the old ones now.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: You don't look it.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Ah-ha, you think so too?!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Then I take it back—see, I've been telling them all, my mind's as sharp as ever!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: It's just this blasted prosthetic leg—the socket always stings on rainy days...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Less talk.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: How long until you give?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: How long until I give is hardly important.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: What matters is, Madam Degenbrecher, how long until you give?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: You can try me and see.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Now both sides have made their move.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: It seems Degenbrecher can still bear out for the moment. Harold is saving his strength, and his bombers and Casters are all but smelling the roses.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Your wine may not have been wasted after all, Enciodes.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: What of Weiss and Matterhorn?
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: I've sent a team of Tschäggättä to find them.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Given what reports have returned so far, the two were likely taken by surprise.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Viscount Craigavon wouldn't place them in mortal danger. That takes senility, and he has none.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: We can only hope.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Our people are en route to the station to stand by. They'll send us word immediately once they intercept.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: May it be that our guest arrives on time.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: What of the merchants that just contacted you?
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: They won't be too daring for now.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Gnosis, pass word onto the Saintess for me—
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: You can save that step!
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: I'm right here. If you have something to say, say it to me in person, Sir Enciodes.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Saintess.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: The Silverashes are disgraced to have allowed such a spiral of events on ceremony grounds. Once the ceremony is over, I will personally take myself to the Vine-Bear Court to apologize to you, Saintess.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: But for now, I fear the ceremony will need to be postponed for another while.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: As it should. Your message is loud and clear, Sir Enciodes.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: If there is anything I can do, I ask you continue to come to me directly.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: And not exploit that my own conscience might force me to see you first.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Saintess, praise thy benevolence.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: But you and the Court devotees must be prudent right now. After you resume this ceremony yourself, Saintess, that will suffice to appease the people.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Degenbrecher's strength needs no introduction. A promise from her is exceedingly rare, and in the event she makes one, it's never broken.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: I think we should give her our full confidence.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Is your confidence that Degenbrecher can fight one against a thousand, or that she has the disregard to die valiantly, in perfect service to your schemes?
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Degenbrecher is ahead confronting the Victorians, and I know her mentality. She holds that, her own reputation aside, the slate with Kjerag can still be wiped clean should anything go wrong.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: She... wait, did she tell you this herself?
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: She defends Kjerag's dignity as one of Her plain, ordinary citizens.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Saintess, do you believe that I bluntly ordered her? Provoked her?
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Even I might say she's changed some. Thus I've trusted her this once—I've gambled on her.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Had I not, you might have watched that affable Viscount lose his life to a few 'panicked tourists'.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: We gamble for a best case scenario.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: 'Gamble'.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: I have always considered the success or failure of anything to hinge on one's own grasp, and not entreaties to gods.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Nothing goes unaccounted for. I put all the chips down. I see it through, win or lose. I've never complained about it.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Sir Enciodes.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Unclasp your hands. You've bruised yourself.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: I ask you pray for Degenbrecher, Great Saintess.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Weiss!
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Wake up, Weiss!
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Nngh...
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Matterhorn...?
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Where... I...?
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: —! Shit! The Victorians are changing it up! Their goal can't be that simple!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: We have to contact the Master!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Gk—*hiss*—
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Stay still, Weiss!
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: If they even managed to subdue and lock up both you and me, then our squad's people can't have escaped either. I've tried, but brute strength alone isn't going to free us.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: It's light outside... It looks like it's day already.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Where are the Victorians?
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: All gone.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Unfortunately... they've probably swarmed the ceremonial grounds.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Matterhorn, help me out here.
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: What do you need?
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: I hide a razor in my shoe's upper.
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: If you can just take it out, Matterhorn... and toss me it!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Don't be insane!
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: What are you using that razor for? In your position? Do you not value your hands?!
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: I have to try.
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: The Master gave me this mission, and I couldn't complete it.
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: And if that's forced him into a passive situation, then I...
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: In any case, even if I'm too late, and he doesn't need it, I'm still going to redeem what isn't lost! I have to make up for my disappointment!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: I suppose you're right.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Matterhorn heaves his body around, laying his fingers over the curve of Weiss's boot.

But what follows betrays Weiss's hopes. He doesn't toss the razor over, but instead pinches the paper-thin tool of murder between his fingers, and with great effort, strains and slashes at the rope over Weiss's wrists.
In its tenuous grip, the blade slips down between his fingers, and cuts into their pulp. Vivid red blood trickles down his wrist.
Matterhorn!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Your hand!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: It'll be fine. It's just a scratch.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: You were going to do the same thing, weren't you?
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: You do have a point, Weiss. The Master's expecting us. We can't leave him waiting too long.
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Just give me one moment, and I can get this rope cut!
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: Matterhorn...
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Umm...
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Who's there?!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: I'm not your enemy.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Sorry, you two were having a moment, weren't you?
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Monch?
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Didn't you leave Kjerag?
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: About that... well, I'll explain in full later.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Madam Sciurus sent me out to scout. That's how I found you all tied up in this Victorian camp.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Where are the others?
attributes.name: Matterhorn

attributes.content: I already set them free.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Anyway, both of you, get going. The Victorians kicked off battle at Lake Silberneherze.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: We need to be there as soon as we can.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Damn it! She can't hold for long!
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: As if I can sit here and look on!
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: You get back here, Arctosz!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Do you seriously think you have the monopoly on righteous anger, Arctosz? We wish we could step in! If your eyes are shot, then try using your brain!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: You acting will definitively ruin things!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Stooping behind others so I can feel sorry for myself runs counter to the Paleroche clan's blood!
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: I can't bear to see this!
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: Bear to see it, you baby!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Someone here is having a harder time watching than you, I guarantee.
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Ten years that Degenbrecher's lived in Kjerag, hasn't she? Just to be some sacrificial pawn here?
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: If today Enciodes can't settle all this, then no amount of achievement, no spoil for Kjerag, could ever convince me to lend him an ear again.
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: I'm far from the grand actor the rest of you would be! I cannot be as calm as any of you are!
attributes.name: Arctosz

attributes.content: And it's too little, too late for that.
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: All you and I can do now is believe in her.
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: I won't be arranging treatment for your wounded hands, then. Remember to hide it with gloves when the time comes.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Also, I imagine the Tschäggättä's report aligns with your gut.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: We can't count on Degenbrecher lasting much longer.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: She's no longer evading.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: She's acting how she used to in her Kazimierz competition days.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Only, afterwards...
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Afterwards, as she fled the assassins with you, she amended that habit.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Any lack of care by her at that point, and you'd die sooner than she did.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Quite.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Still no word from your end?
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: None.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: My investigators already returned. They're sure your guest boarded the train in question to Lake Silberneherze. If anything, it should have arrived just as the ceremony wound down.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: As it is, it'll still take some time until that train arrives.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: I see...
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Gnosis, never have I feared any wager.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Every step that I take, that I've ever taken, I've staked it all.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: This time is no different.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: I believe myself to be sufficiently prepared.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: And yet, I find my patience is made of poorer stuff.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Thank you for telling me what's on your mind, and I know what you want to hear me say. I'll say it for you.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: If you want to ensure The Black Knight's life, or you don't believe she can last until the end, then give the order now. I can tell you, there are still odds of success.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: The archers and Casters at our call are best of the best. Blow up the lake's surface, create confusion, and draw the civilians and soldiers both into midwinter's icy pocket.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Enciodes, the decision lies with you—
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Whatever you do, I will support it. But whatever you do, you carry the consequences in kind.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Those consequences are no simple political game. You might fail to even bear them. That, I can determine for you.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: One quick question. If it were you?
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Then the great winter swim would already be in full swing.
attributes.name: Gnosis

attributes.content: Hah.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Let's trust in Degenbrecher.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Trust she won't fall.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.text: At some unknown point, the first wound appears on her body.
It lies about her shoulder, a slash over her suit, an imperceptible trace of blood drawn.
Compared to the kinds of wounds she's used to, this one's worth no mention.
Degenbrecher fells the few soldiers about her. Ironically, the subtle sting only sharpens the heady mix of fear her eyes strike into you, makes her movements that much more steely cold.
The second wound is brought on by Originium Arts.
An average caster means nothing to Degenbrecher, but the numbers advantage mutates the nature of the Originium Arts' efficacy.
The casters among the troops cast behind their human wall. Fire, ice and thunder burst forth in unison, with staggering momentum.

Degenbrecher flings her weapons, running one of the casters' shoulders clean through, while she stubbornly approaches through the full length of their Arts' range, and plows straight into the soldiers' midst. That puts an end to that display.
The third wound comes as the artillerymen aim a third ballista volley at her.
An opponent armed to the teeth is no fear of Degenbrecher's, but with limbs less than free, and ballistae pestering her in spades, it does get a little annoying to cope.
A shell slips through, and lands a scorch mark on her abdomen.
Her skin is seared in an instant, but hardly any blood comes. That's good, all things considered.
Degenbrecher is under no impression she'll lose.
She's just not too sure she has enough blood to last much longer.

attributes.content: It's not enough...
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Again!
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Urgh!
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: Lisburn!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Charles! Withdraw Lisburn to the rear!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: You staunch his bleeding, I'll be right there with first aid—!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: *cough*...
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: She's giving out!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier E

attributes.content: Now's our chance! Charge!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier F

attributes.content: Hah.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: As long as I can still move a finger...
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Khakkhhh!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: I can handle any of you.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Madam Degenbrecher!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Surely you're reaching your limits too?!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: If you really meant to fight us out-and-out, you wouldn't have drawn out this situation in the first place!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Fight like this any longer, and I fear death will come for somebody...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Isn't that exactly the kind of war you Victorians make an art of starting?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: The only difference here is, your opponent is me alone.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Harold, you're a soldier.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: And I—am your enemy.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: ...Ha-hah, and keenly put, Madam Degenbrecher.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: But I don't believe for a second that you're blind to it.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Karlan Trade's private operations were ferreted out by the Trilby Ashers, and I don't think the Duke will rest on her laurels about it!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: That—*cough*—is Enciodes's problem.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: This is the very last chance they're leaving Master Enciodes!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: He need only bend an ear to the Duke, he need only part with a sliver of the cake...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Be it just 30% of what we proposed! I could still take that back to the Duke and try, for heaven's sakes!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: This was never even a war you needed to win...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: How stupid.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Who do you say that as?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You're window dressing. You're a tourist. You're a burdenbeast vet.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Have you been at leisure for so long, you've begun to believe your own lies?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: —No.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You've never forgotten who you are.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You hate war, absolutely.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You abandoned what real power was in your hands. You took what men of yours sympathized. You left the maelstrom far behind, and fled to Kjerag.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: To a land where you thought war could never really happen.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: But you were still a Victorian inside.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: It wasn't even something you had to remind yourself.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You might say that.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I am a Victorian soldier, Madam.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: That much is ordained, and I might loathe it, and I might flee it.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: But I could never sully Victoria's interests.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: I'm the same.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Is she the same as this Victorian?
They don't seem very identical.
She's Leithanien-born, Kazimierz-raised, and only then came to Kjerag.
They don't need to know her name. All they know is she's born to fight solo, a victor of the knight competitions, the only one to ever win three years running.
Turn the clock further back, and she's a freak cut off from Originium Arts, a pariah in Leithanien.
Gaining and losing any of these things is dead simple.
They bore her to death.
But now, what she has isn't so easily lost, and she has no plans to lose them.
Now, they are the same.
This dull chat—*cough*—ends here.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: I feel all too sorry for you, Madam Degenbrecher.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Oh, would that we hadn't come to this point. But if you wish it, then I choose to respect it.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I must stress at this closing hour that I am, through and through, your fan. The show you made in besting each opponent dazzled like nothing else.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: This and this alone I ask you to believe. It cannot be lied.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Hah.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Noted.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: It's my honor.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Riddled with scars, she raises her degenbrechers once more.
Just as she did in her first appearance before them all, Degenbrecher's point stabs into the ice.
The mist, constant over Lake Silberneherze, parts. A subdued, gargantuan rumble sinks in her enemies' stomachs.
Kchk. Kchk.
There comes the fine sound of cracking, and it's deafening.
Time to end this.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: —! Order to all units!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Stop her breaking the ice! Regroup ASAP! Put down 'The Black Knight of Kazimierz'!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Nothing.
It's not in here.
Oh, and it's not here either.
Well, that just leaves...
Excuse me, sir, the train is speeding up! If you must wander, then please watch your step!
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: Oh, right, you haven't received your complimentary gift yet, have you? Can I ask what you'd like?
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: As compensation for your journey's delay, your purchase is completely free this time!
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: No need.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: But, sir, it's a free gift...
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: Then I give this gift to you, madam.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Er, but, that's not...
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: Take it.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Now excuse me, if I could pass through?
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: A—Alright!
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: Thank you.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: *huff*... *pant*...
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: Urp... oh, what in the land?
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: My legs are a little wobbly...
attributes.name: Conductor

attributes.content: (Now, only the last cabin remains.)
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: (After all this time running around, I'm ragged.)
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: (I could retire... *sigh* Not when Londinium's still refinding its footing. Her Grace would never let me.)
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: (What will I find behind this door?)
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: (Their Kjerag Defense, hidden until this very moment, buried deeper than even their covert transport routes...)
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: (Whatever it is, it's a shame.)
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: It's a shame—Silverash will never get to meet his...
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: What's up, panisko?
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: Sorry, we've got no seats left in our cabin. I think you want to try someplace else.
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: Uh, actually, I can just lea...
attributes.name: Man In a Suit

attributes.content: Did you need something, panisko?
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: I'm not kidding, we're full in here. I mean, you can see. We're bumping shoulders just trying to look around.
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: Yeah, that's why I'm saying I can absolutely just leave and find my own seat! I'm not kidding either!
attributes.name: Man in a Suit

attributes.content: You—You guys seriously don't gotta sit in a cab with me!
attributes.name: Man in a Suit

attributes.content: Don't be like that, Mr. Spokesman. You and us, we're invited together, aren't we? It was all one letter.
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: And this cabin, perfect amount of room for us all to sit. They look after you on the way too.
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: And with us around, the safety problem is no problem.
attributes.name: Silver-clad Knight

attributes.content: Safety's not my problem here, yeah, no...
attributes.name: Man in a Suit

attributes.content: I don't think it's 'perfect', is the thing?? You guys get to sit on the benches and I have to dump my butt on the table!
attributes.name: Man in a Suit

attributes.content: ...Apologies, excuse me.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: I see... I understand. I must be dreaming.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Kazimierz campaign knights and a KGCC representative spokesman sat in the same private cabin of a railway car...
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: So this is the defense Silverash plays.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: How bold. How well and truly typical of the clan head's style.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Your Grace, I can't say it was for lack of trying...
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: But while duty might call me to fight a gaggle of campaign knights at once, I... think it's a little out of the question.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: More than a little.
I guess your job's not easy either.
Stay calm.
attributes.name: Sharp

attributes.content: Just passing through.
attributes.name: Sharp

attributes.content: That uniform...
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: ...This is quite the surprise party.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: What is a Rhodes Islander doing here?
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: You'll have to ask my boss.
attributes.name: Sharp

attributes.options: Et tu, Caster's lackey?;Any questions, Mr. Bellingham?

attributes.content: Quite the shocker indeed. I wasn't expecting you in the flesh.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: But the funny thing is, weren't Rhodes Island and Kjerag only meant to be 'business partners'?
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Yes, if there's one thing I can trust, it's my memory.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Many happy returns... 'Doctor'.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: And we have a Rhodes Island Operator here? It seems the dossiers were right—we still haven't full stock of your company's many faces.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Still, that aside for now. No surprise could be more pleasant, meeting you here.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: In all sincerity, I come with open arms this time. After all, I'm not even out of this disguise, and you recognize me by it.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Rhodes Island, you—
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Yeesh, Doctor! A little help here!
Hmm? 'Sup?
attributes.name: Muelsyse

attributes.content: Our stop's coming up! We gotta get the tech packed, Doc...
attributes.name: Muelsyse

attributes.content: Oop? Who're you guys...?
attributes.name: Muelsyse

attributes.content: Doctor, maybe we oughta bug the conductor to go a little faster...
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hey, it's you!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Rhodes Island and Columbia's Rhine Lab... well, well, well.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: I see it's no coincidence you're all here, then.
attributes.name: 'Trilby Asher'

attributes.content: Oh, jeez, I guess someone knows me already.
attributes.name: Muelsyse

attributes.content: Doc, Mr. Sharp, Letobomb, aren't you gonna introduce this hatsy guy to me here?
attributes.name: Muelsyse

attributes.content: Kjarr, I'd like to know. Would Kjeragandr bless the woman waging such a bloody battle for this statue?
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Though she is born from other lands? Though in Kjeragandr, she has oh so little faith?
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Heheh. That's a very easy question, Saintess.
attributes.name: Kjarr

attributes.content: The term 'Kjerag' simply means one who lives there, who adores this land, who finds a home in this nation.
attributes.name: Kjarr

attributes.content: It's no matter whether Kjeragandr recognizes it.
attributes.name: Kjarr

attributes.content: If a person identifies with it from the bottom of their heart, well, who can deny that?
attributes.name: Kjarr

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: No one can deny that. Not even she, herself.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: She is a Kjerag. She already was.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Kjarr, come with me to meet our visitors.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: Our Victorian guests have come to partake in the ceremony. As Saintess, I have to make an adequate response.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: At the very least, I can't go without saying hello.
attributes.name: Enya

attributes.content: I'd like to stress—the danger of this.
attributes.name: Kjarr

attributes.content: But... very well, Saintess.
attributes.name: Kjarr

attributes.content: Matriarch!
attributes.name: Yucatan

attributes.content: Sciurus is back!
attributes.name: Yucatan

attributes.content: She is?!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Some nerve being late... wait, no, I told her to keep out of this! Why did she come HERE?!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Who's saying I can't come?
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: And I didn't just come, I brought some special guests with me too!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: Is this let's-bring-guests timing to you?
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: You make a language out of inane, you silly sister!
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: ...I am NOT being silly.
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: Indeed. Madam Sciurus's hand is deft and wise. I find her admirable.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Ratatos, you'd do well to finally raise your opinion of her.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: ...What the hell is this, Enciodes?
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Madam Sciurus, the guests have arrived safely.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Good! Bring them all in!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: I'm out.
attributes.name: Monch

attributes.content: Master!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Your guests are here already!
attributes.name: Weiss

attributes.content: Your who? These are MY guests I invited!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: You're Madam Sciurus of the Browntail clan?
attributes.name: Campaign Knight

attributes.content: Very pleased you invited us to be part of this ceremony.
attributes.name: Campaign Knight

attributes.content: Sciurus... is this your pleasant surprise?
attributes.name: Ratatos

attributes.content: Uh, duh!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: Let me introduce you all! We have here our campaign knight from the Adeptus Sprawiedliwi Kazimierz, here to celebrate the erection of our statue to Kjeragandr!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: I sent an invitation especially to the Adeptus! That was NOT an easy invitation to make!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: So they're MY guests!
attributes.name: Sciurus

attributes.content: It's just a coincidence, Madam Sciurus.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: I cannot laud you enough that you were able to invite a campaign knight. My guest of honor, meanwhile, would be this fellow—
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Welcome, Sir Spokesman of the General Chamber of Commerce.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Hello to you. I'm taking it you're Mr. Silverash?
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: Good to meetcha, good to meetcha, and hello from my company. Thank you for all the effort of inviting me out to Kjerag.
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: The scenery here in Kjerag, supremely beautiful. I believe your company and mine will absolutely end the day here with a partnership we both love.
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: Oh, and don't mind me but I gotta say, I think I saw some mad fight out on a frozen lake the whole way here?
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: And kind of familiar too, like, one guy. I mean, those combat moves, they rang bells in my head.
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: Oh sorry, excuse me if I'm talking too much?
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: It's, uh, a holdover from the old job. Ahem. Right, I'll be careful not to say too much that doesn't work towards us working together.
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: No, Mr. Mob, I'm in need of your exact talent right now.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Come again? You need...?
attributes.name: Spokesman Mob

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Right now, this very moment.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Please, come with me. I'll have them cast sound amplification Arts.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: May I ask you to loudly proclaim that—
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: Karlan Trade, and the corporations of the Kazimierz General Chamber of Commerce, are about to sign an agreement.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: To Kazimierz, Kjerag will become a trusty partner.
attributes.name: Enciodes

attributes.content: ...What's that noise?
It's not anyone splashing into the icewater, and it's not cries for help.
It sounds like someone loudly saying something, and then the people all about her stumble in disarray.
That loud voice. But whatever it's saying, she can't tell clearly.
Her field of view narrows and dims by a fraction more. The sounds almost turn to fuzz in her ears.
She can't feel her own limbs anymore, but she can be sure she still has a grip on her old companions.
Her degenbrechers.
Because she knows her body is still acting on reflex, striking down every person that comes near.
It's just... too loud.
Too loud. How can someone talk this noisily?
Why has the crowd gone?
Did someone breach her line of defense already?
No.
The wild beast's dulling eyes of gold suddenly flare alight.
—As long as she can stand.
—She will allow absolutely no one past!
...brecher! Madam Degenbrecher!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Stop fighting... Gah!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: You've lost too much blood, Madam Degenbrecher! Come to your senses a little!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Aht-aht-aht, keep flailing at this rate and you'll sink us both in the lake!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: We're not fighting?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: No more fighting, no more!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Goodness, however much the Duke wants to slap Kjerag in the face, we can't be showing Kazimierz the hand in the process... at least not now.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Kept between Victoria and Kjerag, one might still call it the Duke's personal Silverash grievances. But the moment you bring Kazimierz into it too, things become far, far less simple.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Are the gourmands of Kazimierz already inviting Karlan Trade to the table? With such distance between them, and in such short order?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: What a talented young individual.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: And I know the Duke won't reproach me for deciding to stay my hand. Spiffing excuse.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: A good half my men you batted into the lake, Madam Degenbrecher. It was a backbreaker to scoop them out again...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: If we'd kept going like that, I'd need another pair of arms to treat you all!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I say you need them as is. *cough*
attributes.name: Seasoned Soldier

attributes.content: I take no criticism from anyone still hacking up blood.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: ...We're done?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Well and truly done.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Okay.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Enciodes pulled it off.
She did what she needed to.
That's all Degenbrecher hears.
Now, Madam, stop there!
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: The lives we live, they always tend to be out of our hands.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: I wanted to retire eons ago myself, but I have to keep my own men, my all too often down-and-out brothers in mind.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: With this, it finally ought to be my turn for once, hm?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: And in light of the fact your faithful fan's been beaten black and blue...
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Could you give me your autograph?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: ...You're still in the mood for that?
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: This card... heh.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Do tell?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: The first time I won the Major, they wouldn't leave me alone until I agreed to a photoshoot.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: After that, I never agreed to another one. They were too boring for me.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: I see. No wonder The Black Knight's knight trumps always come in those same poses, edition after edition.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Degenbrecher accepts the pen Harold holds out to her, and writes her name—'Degenbrecher'.
Take it.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: You'd better not have anything else for me to sign.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: Ah, Madam, where are you going?
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Do you need some quick treatment? My first aid's excellent, you know.
attributes.name: Harold

attributes.content: Degenbrecher lifts her head to look to the dawn.
In the distance, two figures walk, approaching her. She still can't make them out, but she knows who they are.
It's like Kjeragandr on high is gazing down on her, someplace as high as the sun.
No need.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: I'm going back.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher

attributes.content: There's people waiting for me.
attributes.name: Degenbrecher
